# Orders Domain Standard

## Purpose

Define the orders bounded context: order creation, status lifecycle, fulfillment tracking, cancellation, and customer order history.

An order is the immutable commercial record of a completed purchase.

---

## Aggregate Root: Order

### Order Entity

```python
class Order:
    id: int
    order_number: str          # unique, human-readable: ORD-00012345
    customer_id: int | None    # null for guest with email only
    guest_email: str | None
    status: OrderStatus
    currency: str

    subtotal: Decimal
    discount_amount: Decimal
    shipping_amount: Decimal
    tax_amount: Decimal
    total_amount: Decimal

    shipping_address: AddressSnapshot
    billing_address: AddressSnapshot
    shipping_method: str

    payment_record_id: int
    checkout_session_id: int

    lines: list[OrderLine]
    status_history: list[OrderStatusChange]

    placed_at: datetime
    version: int
    created_at: datetime
    updated_at: datetime
```

### OrderLine (Entity within Order)

```python
class OrderLine:
    id: int
    order_id: int
    variant_id: int
    quantity: int
    unit_price: Decimal          # immutable snapshot
    line_total: Decimal
    product_snapshot: dict       # {title, sku, attributes, image_url}
```

Product snapshot ensures order history remains accurate after catalog changes.

