## Status State Machine

```
                    ┌─────────────┐
                    │   pending   │ (optional: awaiting payment)
                    └──────┬──────┘
                           │ payment confirmed
                    ┌──────▼──────┐
              ┌─────│  confirmed  │─────┐
              │     └──────┬──────┘     │
              │            │            │
       ┌──────▼──────┐     │     ┌──────▼──────┐
       │  cancelled  │◀────┼─────│  (payment   │
       └─────────────┘     │     │   failed)   │
                           │     └─────────────┘
                    ┌──────▼──────┐
                    │ processing  │
                    └──────┬──────┘
                           │
                    ┌──────▼──────┐
                    │   shipped   │
                    └──────┬──────┘
                           │
                    ┌──────▼──────┐
                    │  delivered  │
                    └─────────────┘

       refunded ◀── (from confirmed/processing/shipped via refund flow)
```

### Valid Transitions

| From | To | Trigger |
|------|-----|---------|
| pending | confirmed | Payment succeeded |
| pending | cancelled | Payment failed / timeout |
| confirmed | processing | Warehouse picks order |
| confirmed | cancelled | Customer/admin cancel (pre-ship) |
| processing | shipped | Carrier label created |
| processing | cancelled | Admin cancel (exception) |
| shipped | delivered | Delivery confirmation |
| confirmed/processing/shipped | refunded | Refund processed |

Invalid transitions raise `InvalidStatusTransition` domain error.

---

## Status History

Every transition recorded:

```python
class OrderStatusChange:
    order_id: int
    from_status: str
    to_status: str
    changed_at: datetime
    changed_by: str      # system | customer_id | admin_id
    reason: str | None
```

Append-only — never mutate history records.

